President Barack Obama will be delivering his second annual Back-to-School Speech on September 14 at Julia R. Masterman Laboratory and Demonstration School in Philadelphia, PA. The speech is an opportunity for the President to address students across the country and encourage them to study hard, stay in school, and take responsibility for their education. The speech will be live streamed on WhiteHouse.gov and more information about watching it can be found at obamawhitehouse.archives.gov/back-to-school. The event is invitation-only and additional media coverage details will be released soon.